Types of variables:
3 types- local, instance and static.
RECAP_______
Local:
the variablse that are declare a method or block of code
PROS: Save memory
CONS: Limited access can not be access out of method or block of code where they are declared

Instance:
The variables which are declared inside a class but out of methodor block of code
PROS: are accessable in all methods of that class
CONS: memory in those variables is occupy for longer time

Static:
If instance variable have a "static" keyword they are called static variables
PROS: Single memory location for all the object of that class
CONS: can hold only one value for all the pbject and stay even onger in the memory then instance var
